I hope this message finds you well. As we look at ways to improve passenger flow through the terminal, I’ve compiled a few concepts that may be worth exploring:

1. Expand and re-configure the security checkpoint to add additional screening lanes, balancing them across peak and off-peak periods.
2. Introduce an intelligent queue-management platform that provides real-time wait-time data and dynamically directs passengers to the shortest lines.
3. Pilot biometric identity verification (e.g., face or iris recognition) at boarding-pass scan points to shorten the document-check stage while maintaining security.
4. Add strategically placed support pillars or columnar way-finding elements that naturally channel foot traffic into clearer lanes, reducing cross-flows in the main concourse.
5. Consider smart, vibration-dampening flooring materials in high-density areas to accommodate surges without compromising comfort or structural integrity.

